  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are several important legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. BCCI (1991)\n- Landmark case involving international banking fraud\n- Established stricter regulations for financial institutions\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major international money laundering investigation\n- Led to significant reforms in banking oversight\n\n3. United States v. Muniz (1994)\n- Defined money laundering as a separate criminal offense\n- Established criteria for prosecuting financial crimes\n\n4. Proceeds of Crime Act (UK, 2002)\n- Comprehensive legislation addressing money laundering\n- Expanded legal framework for investigating financial crimes\n\n5. Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act (RICO)\n- Allowed prosecution of ongoing criminal enterprises\n- Provided tools for addressing systematic financial crimes\n\nThese cases have helped shape modern anti-money laundering legal frameworks and established important precedents for investigating and prosecuting financial crimes.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific cases or precedents?",
